# Observability

rio-build provides three pillars of observability: logs, metrics, and traces.

## Build Log Storage

### Log Lifecycle

<div class="tracey-req" id="r-obs.log.batch-64-100ms"><a class="tracey-req-anchor" href="#r-obs.log.batch-64-100ms">obs.log.batch-64-100ms</a></div>

Log lines are batched (up to 64 lines or 100ms, whichever first) in `BuildLogBatch` messages.

<div class="tracey-req" id="r-obs.log.periodic-flush"><a class="tracey-req-anchor" href="#r-obs.log.periodic-flush">obs.log.periodic-flush</a></div>

The scheduler flushes buffers to S3 periodically (every 30s) during active builds.

## Metrics

### Gateway Metrics

<div class="tracey-req" id="r-obs.metric.gateway"><a class="tracey-req-anchor" href="#r-obs.metric.gateway">obs.metric.gateway</a></div>

| Metric | Type | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `rio_gateway_connections_total` | Counter | Total SSH connections |
| `rio_gateway_connections_active` | Gauge | Currently active connections |
